attributes.Long form description: The student's task is to assemble the IKEA KNARREVIK table. He starts by inspecting the pieces of the table and then proceeds to put the first leg on the shelf. However, he has it the wrong way, once he corrects his mistake, he screws the first leg, but the student tries to screw the top shelf, so the instructor corrects him as this should be the last step. Corrected the mistake, the student starts systematically screwing the hex socket heads of the shelf of the three remaining legs. Once he has screwed the four legs to the shelf, he places the top table on top of the legs so that he can screw them together. Once the top table is in place, the student starts screwing the four legs to the top shelf, then takes the Allen wrench to tighten the hex socket heads from the first set on one side of the furniture and then the other, and finally, the student lifts the furniture and places it in stand position.
